###########################################################

perturbation study for 1D particle distribution
(particles perturbed from constant spacing configuration)

###########################################################

1. reference solution for non disturbed particle distribution with supLen=0.025, dx=0.005
   (where m is obtained by smoothing...)
  
   just by curiosity: 
   comparison of the results of this simulation with the correspodning simulation where m is directly
   calculated based on the particle spacing m=rho*dx and this way initialized via the external .ivs file
   
   
                |    L1    |    L2    |   Linf   |   L1_3   |    L2_3  |  Linf_3  |   L1_2   |   L2_2   |  Linf_2
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
smoothed m      | 0.0608299| 0.0436899| 0.0375259| 0.0222515| 0.0137414| 0.0103771| 0.0170229| 0.0137869| 0.0130829
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 m=rho*dx       | 0.0608562| 0.0438779| 0.0377624| 0.0218631| 0.0136489| 0.0103841| 0.0172189| 0.0140166| 0.0133034

    almost no difference but slight advantage for the smoothed mass...
    KEEP IN MIND: simulation for second case (m=rho*dx) has been comducted with constant tine step dt=0.025, not yet
		  with automatic time control...

2. variation of the perturbation factor<<fac>> in the <<scripts/create_IC1D_SpaceConstRAND.cpp>> program;
   <<fac>> is the maximum value in percent of dx of the uniform perturbation with mean 0.
   


